# ROVEXO Super Admin Architecture

## Single account, single super admin

- One platform role: `super_admin` (singleton enforced in DB).
- Route: `/super-admin` — Mission Control v2 is the home dashboard.
- Legacy `/admin/*` redirects to `/super-admin`. Do not add parallel admin stacks.

## Canonical module registry

SSOT: `lib/super-admin/command-center/registry.ts`

- Every Super Admin module must be registered here with `id`, `href`, `category`, `status`.
- Do not add duplicate “basic” pages when an enterprise engine exists.

## Canonical commerce routes

| Domain | Canonical route |
|--------|-----------------|
| Listings / moderation | `/super-admin/moderation` |
| Orders | `/super-admin/orders-engine` |
| Payments | `/super-admin/payments-engine` |
| Wallet | `/super-admin/wallet-engine` |
| Shipping | `/super-admin/shipping-engine` |

Legacy paths (`/super-admin/listings`, `/orders`, `/payments`) redirect to canonical routes.

## Database Command Center

SSOT: `lib/super-admin/database-health/`

- Production UI: `/super-admin/database`
- API: `/api/super-admin/database`
- Read-only: migrations list, core table counts, storage buckets, connection health.
- No arbitrary SQL execution in production UI.

## API & auth

- All `/api/super-admin/*` routes require `requireApiSuperAdmin()`.
- Mutations must call `auditSuperAdminAction()`.
- Prefer enterprise engine pattern: `reader.ts` + `engine.ts` + descriptor in `lib/enterprise-architecture/registry.ts`.

## Do not

- ❌ Create duplicate nav registries without updating `command-center/registry.ts`
- ❌ Add new basic list pages when an engine module exists
- ❌ Bypass RLS with client-side Supabase for admin operations
- ❌ Expose service-role keys or raw SQL consoles in production
